The new book by 9-year Pro Athlete, TEDx Speaker and Author Dre Baldwin...

On The First Day, you feel great. The workout is tough, but fun. You say, “I’m DOING this!” 

The Second Day, there’s soreness. But you push through it, and you’re still excited. You say to yourself (with just a bit less enthusiasm), “I’m DOING this!” 

The Third Day, things are… different. You seriously consider quitting this whole getting-in-shape scheme. Your discipline (or lack thereof), is saying (loudly), "allow me to reintroduce myself!"  

The Third Day isn’t confined to the gym. It’s any situation where you know there’s work ahead of you, and you question if you’re willing to be fully present and do that work. The Third Day is any situation in which you don’t quite feel like it and aren’t so excited to work — but there is work to be done. And YOU are responsible for getting it done. The Third Day is the decision that you make at that moment.

The question this book answers: HOW do you bring
